r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-STARS-TEX     06-09 0323
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ZUBOV CASE TO GO TO DISTRICT ATTORNEY TODAY, POLICE SAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Paperwork for the assault case against Stars defenseman Sergei
Zubov is expected to go to the district attorney Tuesday and a
preliminary hearing could be set, said Wade Goolsby, a supervising
captain for the Coppell, Texas, Police Department.
</P>
<P>
   Zubov was arrested early Sunday on suspicion of aggravated
assault-family violence, a second-degree felony, police reports
said. If convicted, Zubov could face two to 20 years in prison and
a $10,000 fine, Goolsby said.
</P>
<P>
   A 911 hangup call prompted police to go to Zubov's Coppell home
at 3:05 a.m. Sunday. An initial investigation indicated that Zubov
had brandished a kitchen knife during an alleged assault involving
his wife, Irina, Goolsby said.
</P>
<P>
   Zubov was released Sunday morning after posting a $5,000 bail,
Goolsby said.
</P>
<P>
   The case will be turned over to the Dallas County District
Attorney's office. SURGERIES AWAIT
</P>
<P>
   The Stars expect to have at least four players undergo surgery
in the next two weeks, coach Ken Hitchcock said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Richard Matvichuk is expected to undergo major knee
surgery to replace the anterior cruciate ligament in his left knee.
Matvichuk played the second half of the season without the ligament
and will have it replaced by one from a cadaver. Matvichuk is in
contract negotiations with the Stars and could wait until he has a
contract before he has the surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Scheduled for minor surgery are goalie Ed Belfour, who is
expected to have arthroscopic surgery on his shoulder; goalie Manny
Fernandez, who is expected to undergo minor wrist surgery; and
defenseman Craig Muni, who is expected to have arthroscopic surgery
on his knee.
</P>
<P>
   Team doctor Dan Cooper has a speaking engagement in late June,
so surgeries will likely be performed before June 21.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
