<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 12:29 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0708 &Cx1f; tab-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HEROIN-METHADONE-TREA     06-09 1943
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEROIN-METHADONE-TREATMENT-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
310-996-0089. 
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  
 FOR HEROIN ADDICTION, METHADONE and OTHER TREATMENT OPTIONS  
 &HT;     (This is the fourth in a five-part series on America's
mismanaged drug war, by Ethan A. Nadelmann, director of the
Soros-funded Lindesmith Center. For purchase information _ the
rates are not prohibitive -- contact one of these New York Times
Syndicate sales representatives: 
 &HT;    (--U.S., Canada and the Pacific: CONNIE WHITE in Kansas City at
1-800-444-0267 or 816-822-8448, or fax her at 816-822-1444. 
 &HT;    (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: PAUL FINCH in Los Angeles, 310-996-0075; fax, By ETHAN A. NADELMANN  
