<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CRIME-HOTSPOTS (Albany, N.Y.) _ New York Gov. George Pataki has
announced a pilot program to help counties share crime data, map
trends and nab more criminals. It's modeled after New York City's
successful effort to that turns dry crime statistics into maps of
criminal hot spots. By TRACEY TULLY.
</P>
<P>
   BUSTAMANTE (San Antonio) _ Former Congressman Albert Bustamante,
D-Texas, officially ended his prison sentence for racketeering and
bribery this week. As he began serving two years of probation, he
said a coalition of Hispanic organizations in California is seeking
a presidential pardon for him. By JACQUE CROUSE.
</P>
<P>
   JURORS-RECANT (San Antonio) _ Minutes after Joe Kennedy was
sentenced in May to probation for raping a female employee of his
downtown Irish pub, five jurors told him they had made the wrong
decision. Now a Texas judge must decide whether the jurors can
testify as part of a motion for a new trial. By MELISSA PRENTICE.
</P>
