   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-JEWS (Havana) _ The first Jews arrived in Cuba at the
beginning of the 20th century. In the years before World War II,
they prospered and their ranks grew. But decades of a U.S. embargo
coupled with other Cuban troubles have diminished their ranks so
that a dedicated core today struggles to survive. By CECILE S.
HOLMES. (Photo available on New York Times photo service)
</P>
