   LIVING-COLUMN-HAHN (Undated) There's nothing like being a kid in
summer.
</P>
<P>
   By Jon Hahn. (story will move in the ``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   DIRECTOR-FITZGERALD (Seattle) Movie about out-of-the-closet
travails reflects Canadian director's life.
</P>
<P>
   By Paula Nechak. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-MITCHARD (Seattle) Jacquelyn Mitchard knows what a
difference that Oprah can make in a writer's career. This longtime
journalist had her first novel, ``The Deep End of the Ocean,''
picked as the first offering of the Oprah Book Club in June 1996
and went on to become a phenonmenon. Now, this nationally
syndicated columnist mother of five returns with her next novel,
``The Most Wanted.'' A talk with Mitchard on book fame and good
fortune.
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
