   The most dangerous place in Washington these days is between
this prosecutor and potential evidence.
</P>
<P>
   This week was pretty good for Starr-gazers. The prosecutor
declared that Clinton was under ``serious criminal investigation.''
His spokesman said that Clinton himself might soon receive a
subpoena, requiring that he testify under oath about his cordial
friendship with Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
   Lewinsky herself, as if rattled, abruptly changed her lawyers.
</P>
<P>
   Starr, having won a legal battle over the right to require
Sidney Blumenthal, a presidential aide, to testify, filed a brief
with the Supreme Court, urging that he be let loose on various
