</P>
<P>
   BAPTISTS (Salt Lake City) _ The Southern Baptists, meeting at
their annual convention, are expected to pass an addition to their
creed that says ``a wife is to submit graciously to the servant
leadership of her husband'' and serve as his ``helper in managing
the household and nurturing the next generation.'' The statement by
the Baptists, which number 16 million in the United States, is
believed to be one of the strongest official statements in this
direction of any large mainstream religious faith and is aimed at
correcting what they see as the ``decay of the family.'' By Gustav
Niebuhr.
</P>
