<HEADLINE>
FOUR DAUGHTERS FOR BILL AND CAMILLE COSBY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Does Bill Cosby have any children other than the son who
died?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.J., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Bill Cosby and his wife, Camille, have four daughters: Erika,
Erinn, Ensa and Evin. The comedian married Camille Hanks on Jan.
25, 1964, while she was attending the University of Maryland.
</P>
<P>
   Ennis Cosby was shot to death on Jan. 16, 1997, during an
apparent robbery attempt in Los Angeles. Cosby had stopped his car
to fix a flat tire when he was attacked.
</P>
<P>
   Jury selection began recently in the trial of Mikhail Markhasev,
a 19-year-old Ukrainian immigrant charged in Cosby's murder.
</P>
<P>
   Autumn Jackson, a 23-year-old woman who claims to be Bill
Cosby's daughter, began serving a five-year prison sentence in
April for trying to extort $40 million from Cosby.
</P>
<P>
   Cosby testified at the trial that he had an affair with
Jackson's mother in 1974 but does not believe he is the woman's
father.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How would I go about getting information on tenants' rights?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.F., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The Fort Worth Human Relations Commission publishes a Fair
Housing Directory for Tarrant County residents, said Angelica
Orozco, an office assistant with the commission.
</P>
<P>
   The free booklet details the rights of tenants and landlords.
For a copy, write to the Fort Worth Human Relations Commission, 908
Monroe St., Fort Worth, TX 76102, or call 871-7525.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What is the mailing address for New Braunfels' Wurstfest and
the dates when it will be this year?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.V., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Wurstfest, a festival in Landa Park on the banks of the Comal
River, will be Oct. 30-Nov. 8.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets are $6 at the gate and $5 in advance, but children under
age 12 are admitted free. Scheduled performers include accordionist
Myron Floren, who performed with Lawrence Welk for many years, and
polka musician Jimmy Sturr.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (800) 221-4369 or write to the
Wurstfest Association, Box 310309, New Braunfels, TX 78131-0309.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
