Delphi Chassis in Kettering, for example, could face shutdown as
early as next week if strike lingers, union officials say.
Meanwhile, local economic experts discuss the financial fallout
from the woes in Flint. (Drummond, Dayton Daily News) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
