<P>
   SPORTS-HALL _ WACO, Texas _ Picture a young sports fan crouching
behind home base while a virtual-reality Nolan Ryan winds up on the
mound and pitches a fastball, which then lands with a thud in the
young catcher's mitt. Hall of fame supporters are hoping by 2000 to
raise $2.5 million to almost double the size of the museum and add
more interactive exhibits, educational programs and a sports
research library. (Smith, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BOHLS-COLUMN _ AUSTIN _ One cannot blame R.C. Slocum for never
going to another baseball game in his life, and it's got nothing to
do with the designated hitter. Baseball could cost the Texas A&AMP;M
football coach three prize football players, or almost 20 percent
of his last recruiting class. It will surprise no one if
quarterback Chip Ambres, wide receiver Choo Freeman and tight end
Greg Porter sign major-league baseball contracts and forego their
college football careers. (Bohls, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
