   &UR; DANCE  &LR;  DANCE-JACOBS-PILLOW (Undated) _ On June 23, when the
nation's oldest summer dance festival opens in tiny Becket, Mass.,
it will have a new director, Ella Baff. Running Jacob's Pillow
Dance Festival is hard work, but Ms. Baff is full of ambitious
visions. By Jennifer Dunning.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POP MUSIC  &LR;  COLTRANE-JAZZ (New York) _ It is a perfect
indicator of jazz's restricted place in American society that Ravi
Coltrane _ who is the son of John Coltrane _was nobody special as a
boy growing up in Woodland Hills, a suburb of Los Angeles, far away
from the bohemian world. By Ben Ratliff.
</P>
