<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, June 10, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington, D.C.) Judge sets procedural
matters for the September Microsoft antitrust trial.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (story will move in the ``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   JAVA-CONSERVATIVE (Sumner, Wash.) With a slogan whose theme
dates back to a 1960 speech by Barry Goldwater _ ``The coffee
that's taking America back!'' _ a Sumner-based coffee company is
targeting its sales to right-thinking Americans. The Original
Conservative Coffee Company is marketing roasts with names that
will warm the hearts of Clinton enemies. The blends may be light,
but the humor runs to heavy name-calling and innuendo.
</P>
<P>
