<P>
   Pharmerica Inc., Tampa, Fla., agreed to acquire National
Institutional Pharmaceutical Services Inc., Owings Mills, Md., a
unit of Integrated Health Services Inc., for undisclosed terms.
</P>
<P>
   Allen Telecom Inc., Beechwood, Ohio, a supplier of
wireless-communications products, said it would cut 100 jobs, or 3
percent of its work force, and take an unspecified charge as demand
for its products slows and prices drop.
</P>
<P>
   Symantec Corp., Cupertino, Calif., a maker of computer-virus
detection programs, said it would buy back up to 5 percent, or $63
million, of its stock. The company has about 56 million shares
outstanding. &QL;
