transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-ABACHA-NYT (moved on Monday, June 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 8,
about the death of Gen. Sani Abacha, the Nigerian leader,
misidentified his predecessor. General Abacha took over in 1993 by
unseating President Ernest Shonekan, an unelected civilian leader
for two and a half months, not Gen. Ibrahim Babangida, who had
installed Mr. Shonekan.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BRODY-HEALTH-NYT (moved on Monday, June 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 8,
about new weight guidelines, misstated an alternate formula for
computing body mass. The formula, which was given correctly in a
chart, entails squaring height, not weight.
</P>
<P>
   BC-STILLMAN-FILMS-NYT (moved on Friday, May 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, May 29,
about the movie director Whit Stillman credited him with an award
incorrectly. The winner of the 1990 Oscar for best screenplay was
Bruce Joel Rubin for ``Ghost,'' not Mr. Stillman for
``Metropolitan.''
</P>
</TEXT>
