<SLUG> BC-NY-NJ-ARRESTS-RAPE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
7 TEENS ACCUSED OF RAPING GIRL, 15 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By CHARLIE LeDUFF   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Seven Staten Island teen-agers have been accused of raping a
15-year-old New Jersey girl after luring her to a motel room in a
resort town on the south Jersey shore, where police said the young
men gave her alcoholic drinks and photographed the sexual assault,
authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The girl, whose name was not released because of the nature of
the crime, was attacked by the seven teen-agers on Sunday around 5
p.m., said Capt. John Harkins of the North Wildwood Police
Department. She was taken to Burdette Tomlin Memorial Hospital,
where she was treated and released, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The teen-agers, who range in age from 16 to 18 years old,
assaulted the girl shortly after meeting her and a friend on the
boardwalk that lines Wildwood Island, about 45 miles south of
Atlantic City, Harkins said.
</P>
<P>
   The girls were on a school trip and had been staying on the
island for the weekend, authorities said. They decided to sneak
away from the school group and were convinced by the boys to return
to their room at the Grey Manor Motel at 2100 Surf Ave. in
Wildwood, about two and a half miles from the motel where the girls
were staying in Wildwood Crest, Harkins said.
</P>
<P>
   Once there, Harkins said, the girls were given alcohol. The
group partied for a period of time before one girl left the room
and walked back to the motel where the school group was staying.
The girl alerted a chaperone, who telephoned police, Harkins said.
</P>
<P>
   The chaperone later found the 15-year-old disoriented and
wandering the Boardwalk, police reported. Authorities then went to
the Grey Manor Motel, where the boys were arrested and police
seized photos that were taken by the suspects during the assault,
Harkins said.
</P>
<P>
   The 18-year-olds were identified as Jared McCleary Moore, a
resident of the Dongan Hills section of Staten Island; Gary Thomas
Stark and Marques Cardin Parker, whose addresses were not
immediately known. Police did not release the names of the other
four teen-agers because they are juveniles _ three are 17 years old
and the other is 16. All have been charged with aggravated sexual
assault.
</P>
<P>
   As of Tuesday night, Moore was still being held in the Cape May
County Jail because he was unable to post the $15,000 bail, an
administrator at the jail said. Phone calls to his family's home
were not returned.
</P>
</TEXT>
